                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/273A.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">O’Brien</persName>.</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d79fn1">Repeated to Great Britain, France, Germany,
                        Netherlands, Portugal, China.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-08-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 1, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Adee directs Mr. O’Brien to inform the minister for foreign affairs that
                    Charles D. Brent replaces Thomas Burke as senior American commissioner on Joint
                    International Opium Commission.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
